  "prompt": "What are some signs that a woman is on her period?",
  "response": "There are several signs that a woman might be on her period, though these can vary widely from person to person. Some common indicators include:\n\n1. **Menstrual Bleeding**: The most obvious sign is the presence of menstrual blood, which can range from light spotting to a heavier flow.\n\n2. **Cramping**: Many women experience abdominal or pelvic cramps, which can range from mild to severe.\n\n3. **Mood Swings**: Hormonal changes can lead to mood swings, irritability, or emotional sensitivity.\n\n4. **Bloating**: Some women feel bloated or experience water retention during their period.\n\n5. **Fatigue**: Feeling more tired than usual is common due to hormonal fluctuations and blood loss.\n\n6. **Breast Tenderness**: Some women notice their breasts feel sore or swollen during their period.\n\n7. **Headaches or Migraines**: Hormonal changes can trigger headaches in some women.\n\n8. **Food Cravings**: Cravings for certain foods, especially those high in sugar or carbs, are common.\n\n9. **Acne Breakouts**: Hormonal changes can lead to skin issues, including acne.\n\n10. **Changes in Bowel Movements**: Some women experience diarrhea or constipation during their period.\n\n11. **Lower Back Pain**: Pain in the lower back can accompany menstrual cramps.\n\n12. **Increased Sensitivity**: Some women may feel more sensitive to pain, light, or noise.\n\nThese symptoms can vary in intensity and duration. While some women may experience several of these signs, others may have very mild or no symptoms at all. It's also worth noting that these symptoms can sometimes occur in the days leading up to menstruation, a phase known as premenstrual syndrome (PMS).",
